# HTML and Liquid Template Guidelines

This site uses Jekyll's Liquid templating with a single-page layout.

## Main Template Structure
[index.html](mdc:index.html) contains the complete page layout with these sections:

### HTML Head
- Meta tags for responsive design and SEO
- External CDN resources (Google Fonts, Font Awesome, Academicons)
- Local assets: [js/index.js](mdc:js/index.js), [css/bulma.min.css](mdc:css/bulma.min.css), compiled CSS
- Site title uses `{{ site.name }}` variable

### Navigation
- Fixed-top Bulma navbar with burger menu for mobile
- Navigation items from [_data/navigation.yml](mdc:_data/navigation.yml)
- Uses `{% for item in site.data.navigation %}` loop

### Content Sections
1. **Hero/About**: Profile image and bio from `{{ site.description }}`
2. **Publications**: Loops through [_data/publications.yml](mdc:_data/publications.yml)
3. **Teaching**: Hardcoded teaching assistant information
4. **Projects**: Loops through [_data/projects.yml](mdc:_data/projects.yml)
5. **Miscellaneous**: Loops through [_data/misc.yaml](mdc:_data/misc.yaml)
6. **Hobbies**: Content from [_data/hobbies.yml](mdc:_data/hobbies.yml)

### Shared Template
[_includes/section.html](mdc:_includes/section.html) handles rendering for publications, projects, and misc items:
- Conditional link logic based on available fields (`project_page`, `webpage`, `paper`, `arxiv`)
- Author rendering with highlighting for `author.is_me`
- Button generation for various link types (Paper, Video, GitHub, etc.)

## Liquid Template Patterns

### Data Access
- `site.data.filename` - Access YAML data files
- `site.variable` - Access [_config.yml](mdc:_config.yml) variables
- `publication.field` - Access item properties in loops

### Control Structures
- `{% for item in collection %}...{% endfor %}` - Loop through data
- `{% if condition %}...{% endif %}` - Conditional rendering
- `{% assign variable = value %}` - Variable assignment

### Filters
- `| relative_url` - Make URLs relative to site base
- `| markdownify` - Convert markdown to HTML
- `| remove: '<p>'` - Remove unwanted HTML tags

## Best Practices
- Keep personal info in [_config.yml](mdc:_config.yml) variables
- Use data files for content that changes frequently
- Maintain consistent URL patterns and link structures
- Ensure responsive design with Bulma classes
- Test all external links and social media integrations

When editing templates, preserve the existing Liquid logic and ensure proper data binding from YAML files.
